  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Aarti, today is a good day for cooking? I love the smell of pav bhaji. What dish are you making today?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I just made chicken curry with jeera rice. Pav bhaji is my favorite too, but I wanted something lighter today. Want a taste? 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Aarti, you said \"Want a taste?\" — small fix: we say \"Would you like a taste?\"  \nYour chicken curry sounds delicious. Is this a family recipe?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yes, it is my mom's recipe. She always adds a bit of garam masala at the end. I try to follow it exactly, but sometimes I get the timing wrong and the chicken becomes a little dry. 🥲 But overall, it turned out okay today!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Aarti, you said \"the chicken becomes a little dry\" — small fix: we say \"the chicken becomes a bit dry.\"  \nCooking like your mom is a sweet tradition. Did you play any music while cooking today?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "No, today I didn't play music, but I often listen to ghazals while cooking. They help me relax. How about you? Do you enjoy music while working?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Aarti, you said \"I enjoy music while working\" — perfect sentence!  \nGhazals are so calming. I listen to old songs while grading papers. What ghazal singer is your favorite?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "My favorite is Lata Mangeshkar. Her voice is so soothing. Sometimes I also listen to Jagjit Singh. His ghazals are very emotional. But Lata is my first choice. Do you like Hindi music?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Aarti, you said \"Lata is my first choice\" — small fix: we say \"Lata is my first choice singer.\"  \nLata Mangeshkar’s voice is timeless. I love her too! Do you have a favorite song of hers?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "My favorite is \"Pyar Hua Ikrar Hua.\" It gives me such a peaceful feeling. I often sing it while studying, but I’m not very good! 😊 I think I should go now. Have to revise some notes. Talk to you soon, Maya!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Aarti, you said \"Talk to you soon, Maya!\" — small fix: we say \"Talk to you soon, Miss Maya!\"  \n\"Pyar Hua Ikrar Hua\" is beautiful. Sing it proudly — I’d love to hear you again. Study well!"
    }
  ],
